parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission slips or hesitates
the engine RPMs increase without acceleration
the vehicle fails to shift into gear
or the vehicle stalls or dies while driving.
